    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-27T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-27T10:30:00-05:00" n="907"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea (<persName corresp="#p_BEO1"
                            type="from">Briggs</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-28T00:00:00+08:30"
                            >June 28, 1954—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1398. Repeated information Tokyo 831, Taipei 117, Saigon 45. Tokyo pass <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Announcement last December of withdrawal US Forces<note n="1" xml:id="d907fn1"
                        >Reference was to the statement of Dec. 26; see footnote 1 <ref
                            target="#pg_1679">p. 1679</ref>.</note> was not well received by
                    President <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> because he regarded it as
                    unrelated to <pb facs="0698" n="1816" xml:id="pg_1816"/> broad pattern of
                        US-<gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> relations and US–Asian policy, and
                    being imperfectly understood it increased <persName corresp="#p_RS1"
                        >Rhee</persName>’s apprehension over abandonment. If new redeployment plan
                    is discussed well in advance and explained in terms of our broader objective
                    there is some hope we can obtain <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s
                    understanding and cooperation whereas announcement of plan without proper
                    preparation could be misinterpreted as sign of US weakness and evidence lack of
                    intention support <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> in future.</p>
                <p>Later this week I hope to discuss matter with Generals <persName
                        corresp="#p_HGJE1">Hull</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_TLGMD1"
                        >Taylor</persName>. Pending that conversation my interim view is that it is
                    essential consider redeployment in context entire US-<gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                        >ROK</gloss> relationship. In particular decision should be related to
                    whatever conclusion we reach regarding size <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>
                    Forces (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 1358 and 1383<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d907fn2">Dated June 18 and June 23, <ref target="#pg_1808">pp.
                            1808</ref> and <ref target="#pg_1813">1813</ref>,
                    respectively.</note>).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
